job_description:
Your Impact
In this position, you will contribute to preventing and combating Financial Economic Crime (FEC). You are the link that translates business requirements into a digital solution. It is important to retrieve the right information from the clients, and to proactively advise these clients. For this, knowledge of the FEC domain is important. You advise your clients not only on what is possible, but also feasible. You weigh up the options based on your knowledge of the domain and the technology. You contribute to and monitor the progress of the implementation of changes.


The reasons why this is your dream job:
You will work within a team of experienced consultants in the field of FEC, each fulfilling a role with a client;
You actively contribute to the development of the practice, both in terms of knowledge and quantitative growth;
You are a representative for the practice and actively participate in the FEC community at Ordina;
You discover ‘the question behind the question’ in the area of Financial Economic Crime (FEC);
You dare to ask tough questions;
You think proactively about opportunities for the business and you check ideas for impact and feasibility;
You develop ideas into epics, features and user stories;
You work with end users, product owners and product managers to clarify requirements and translate them into solutions;
You will stay involved in the development, acceptance, implementation and operations to ensure that the intended value is realized and risks are mitigated.

Where you're going to get started
Ordina is the largest independent digital business partner in the Benelux. Within our business unit 'Cybersecurity & Compliance' we help our customers protect their digital business with solutions for cybersecurity, compliance and financial economic crime. The business unit consists of four practices: Financial Economic Crime (FEC), Security Testing & Reporting (red team), Security Operations & Engineering (blue team), and Security Strategy & Maturity (advisory).


Financial Economic Crime is one of Ordina's growth areas, putting it at the heart of our strategy. Ordina Financial Economic Crime (FEC) is a close-knit community of enthusiastic professionals, who together make the difference in innovative projects for our customers. You work in teams where we match people on specialism and personality. We have a strong focus on quality, closely follow the latest trends in AML/CTF and Fraud and share all our knowledge to keep broadening our professionalism. At Ordina FEC you direct your own ambitions and development.

This is you
A professional with passion for this work. You are committed to quality and customer satisfaction. Your organizational sensitivity and judgment enable you to determine what our customers need. You have a positive attitude and are not afraid to make mistakes. You are a strong communicator, proactive, results-oriented, strong analytical skills and you dare to step forward. You strive for continuous improvement, not just for yourself but alsog for your surroundings. You are a team player who is also able to work independently.


Next to that we would love to see:
At least a bachelor of masters degree in Business Administration, Computer Science or similar education;
3 to 6 years of experience with data analysis, business analysis, software implementation and/or ETL tooling;
Knowledge of and experience with Financial Economic Crime (KYC/AML/CTF/Sanctions/Fraud) is a must;
Knowledge of and experience with Agile working, and Scrum in particular;
Experience in drafting requirements and business logic;
Knowledge of and experience with DevOps working methods is a plus;
Experience with SQL skills;
Knowledge and experience within the Finance sector;
Fluency in Dutch and English.

Benefits
At Ordina we offer you the opportunity to work in an environment with colleagues who are passionate about their profession. With us you can grow as a professional by working on assignments at the best companies in the Netherlands and by learning from colleagues. Knowledge development is very important to us, as is contributing to the safety of the Netherlands through our involvement in security communities, education and research.


Ordina wants to offer employees an environment in which they can be themselves and develop optimally. In doing so, our guiding principles are:
Our people are our highest priority;
We are building a learning organization with an open culture;
We do meaningful work with impact for our clients.

As an Ordina employee, you can count on:
Flexible working hours;
20 statutory days off and 7 additional days off via flex benefits;
With "flex benefits" you can customise your terms of employment to suit your personal requirements;
Mobility allowance (choice between a lease car or a transport allowance);
Bonus scheme;
Study and training opportunities; free to grow and develop as you wish;
A pension plan, to which you are not obliged to contribute.


Everyone is welcome to apply. Because we believe in the power of diversity and value inclusion. After all, the best ideas and smartest solutions arise in diverse teams. That is exactly why we pay so much attention to the composition of our high performance teams. So that you feel at home and can get the best out of yourself.

Heijen, Limburg | Full-time | max €6.291,- | Bachelor/WO Degree | Customer Implementation

Arvato has an exciting opportunity for you to grow your career as Operations Manager within a leading full-service SCM company. We believe that business growth starts with an outstanding service focused on innovation that fits exactly to the needs of the market and our customers. That's why Arvato is currently experiencing new customer implementations. This is where you bring your added value to the table with innovative propositions. Within this position your contribution is highly valued and you will set the standards for our successful and futureproof journey for our new customer.

Together with your Director, Warehouse Manager and the rest of the Operation teams you are responsible for the success and growth of this brand new warehouse. As it concerns an new customer implementation, you can completely redesign the organization together with your team. How cool is that!?

If that isn't cool enough.. This new Arvato warehouse will serve an A-Brand who is famous for creating qualitative and innovative technology for their customers.

What will you do as an Operations Manager at Arvato?
You will be responsible for the realization of operational services, in accordance with agreed quality, service and financial objectives. By developing people, processes and automation you will ensure that targets (financial and customer satisfaction) are met. A great team of Warehouse Managers and Lean Experts will report directly to you.

Furthermore you are responsible for:
Total Cost ownership for Warehouse and Operations;
Ensuring that services are implemented/executed in such a way that they can be realized efficiently at the required qualitative and quantitative levels;
Analysis and monitoring of the overall operation and process optimization;
Coordinate Personnel Matters (HR);
Coordinating optimal deployment/use of staff and materials and building strategy for the long-term;
Implementation of change and improvement processes across the entire operation;
Responsible for intensive monitoring of KPIs and delivery of the associated management reports;
Carrying out policy according to legal regulations and safety standards, such as 5S;
Leading, developing and delivering performance improvement plans ensuring the achievement of budgets and overall company performance targets;
Leading and directing the Operations departments ensuring functional objectives (KPIs) are achieved;
Ensuring collaboration between all parties in the entire order-to-cash process and avoid silo-thinking;
Driving performance efficiencies and generating cost efficiencies.

Qualifications you bring with you as an Operations Manager:
Bachelor or Master degree (in for example: Logistics, Business Administration or Engineering)
Extensive demonstrable experience in a contract logistics environment;
Experience in an operations environment;
Knowledge of systems for both the primary and supporting processes (including Microsoft, ERP);
Knowledge of and experience with project management methods (e.g. Prince 2);
Good communication skills, both spoken and written, in English and preferably Dutch;
Analytical and strategic thinking with good business acumen and the ability to think from the 'customers' perspective;
Strong financial knowledge covering budget forecasting.

What we offer
We offer you a challenging and independent full-time position, for 40 hours a week. We have a non-contributory pension, which means that on average you have a higher net salary compared to other companies!
In addition, we offer:
A competitive salary up to € 6.291, - gross a month;
A bonus based on performance and organization results;
Travel allowance;
8% holiday payment;
25 vacation days, possibility to build up to 28 vacation days;
Up to 40% discount on your fitness subscription;
Telephone and laptop;
Collective health insurance;
ANW Insurance and WIA Hiaat insurance, fully paid for by Arvato.

About Arvato Supply Chain Solutions
Arvato is a fast-growing organization with an informal and transparent corporate culture. We are open to ambition, personal development and initiatives. Arvato Supply Chain Solutions is specialized in logistics solutions. In collaboration with the customer, we determine the most effective logistics process that meets their needs. Our DNA is built upon Customer Obsession, Ownership and Continuous Improvement. We achieve our goals by means of experience, state-of-the-art technologies, creativity, passion and a commitment to quality, innovation and having fun!

In the Netherlands, we serve our customer from four locations: Heijen, Venlo, Venray and Schiphol-Rijk, within these locations approximately 1.000 employees are working for Arvato. In addition to classic logistics services such as; warehousing, picking, transport management and comprehensive value-added services, we also offer tailor-made solutions for companies from sectors such as consumer products, high-tech and healthcare. For various customers we take the entire logistics process out of their hands.

Are you the new Operations Manager we are looking for?
Then apply directly via the “Apply” button and upload your CV and motivation letter. Our Recruitment department will contact you for the further process.

